post_text: Our CCCOE Code.org Computer Science (CS) Summer Workshop Week is completed!!! Together through a virtual learning environment, our cohort of 14 CS Principles and 17 CS Discoveries educators from all over our county and region embarked on a week-long summer CS workshop. Our cohort of computer scientists engaged and explored Code.org curriculum to learn and collaborate to bring CS to their students and families. We will follow up with four more professional learning sessions throughout this coming school year to support CS for ALL!
text: Our CCCOE Code.org Computer Science (CS) Summer Workshop Week is completed!!! Together through a virtual learning environment, our cohort of 14 CS Principles and 17 CS Discoveries educators from all over our county and region embarked on a week-long summer CS workshop. Our cohort of computer scientists engaged and explored Code.org curriculum to learn and collaborate to bring CS to their students and families. We will follow up with four more professional learning sessions throughout this coming school year to support CS for ALL!

post_text: Fourteen teachers joined the 2020-2021 CCCOE Code.org Computer Science Cohort. These educators completed a five-day virtual summer workshop to begin teaching AP Computer Science Principles to students beginning this upcoming school year. The five-day workshop included learning about computer science, teaching strategies (including those in a virtual setting), and ensuring equity in computer science education. The goal is to make Computer Science available to all students.
text: Fourteen teachers joined the 2020-2021 CCCOE Code.org Computer Science Cohort. The goal is to make Computer Science available to all students.

Contra Costa County’s school districts announce their 2020-2021 Teachers of the Year:

The school districts in Contra Costa County have proudly submitted their 2020-2021 Teacher of the Year (TOY) candidates to the Contra Costa County Office of Education (CCCOE). The newly honored teachers are not only recognized for their outstanding education achievements, but they also represent the approximately 8,600 teachers educating more than 177,000 students in Contra Costa County’s public schools.

post_text:
Message from County Superintendent:

You might have heard that the Governor made a statement suggesting that schools may not reopen until the fall. At this time, the Department of Education, the Department of Public Health, and the Governor’s Office have not made a decision in this direction. I continue to communicate daily with local public health officials and with our school leaders as we monitor and plan during this situation. I want to assure you that the school leaders throughout Contra Costa are working hard to help support families during this very stressful time. Your schools will continue to communicate with you as the situation evolves and decisions are made.

Please check your school district’s website and social media sites before calling or emailing to see if your questions are answered there. Also, go to http://www.coronavirus.cchealth.org/ or our CCCOE website: http://www.cocoschools.org/coronavirus.

Lynn Mackey
County Superintendent of Schools

On Monday, April 13 Sandy Hook Promise will be hosting a Spring Showcase where students from SAVE Promise Clubs across the Bay Area will come together to share the activities they held at their school this year to promote Sandy Hook Promise messages and discuss their vision for creating safer and more inclusive communities across the Bay.

The event will be held at the Pleasant Hill Community Center for a full day of empowerment and community-building. SHP would love to see you at the showcase. Simply RSVP using this link (also available in the attached detailed invitation): https://sandyhookpromise.wufoo.com/forms/mbqaffe1vi3doq

No worries if you’re not sure of an exact headcount yet, you can give us a rough estimate. If you plan to join us on April 13, please RSVP by EOD Thursday, March 12.

"Brief Intervention for Substance-Using Adolescents"
This training is to build skills of people working with adolescents. Brief Intervention is a short-term intervention that consists of two to four sessions aimed at adolescents who use alcohol, tobacco, and/or other drugs. This approach uses motivational interviewing, cognitive behavior therapy and the stages of change model to meet the needs of adolescents.

post_text:
Breakout-group time at today’s Youth Mental Health First Aid (YMHFA) training. This program teaches the 5-step action plan to offer initial help to young people showing signs of a mental illness or in a crisis.

You are more likely to encounter a young person—friend, family member, student, neighbor, or member of the community—in an emotional or mental crisis than someone having a heart attack. Learning how to help them is critical.

Participants Will Learn Youth Mental Health First Aid teaches a 5-step action plan to offer initial help to young people showing signs of a mental illness or in a crisis, and connect them with the appropriate professional, peer, social, or self-help care.

post_text:
Pittsburg Unified School District will host a substitute teacher casting call on Monday, November 4, 2019 from 4:00pm – 6:00pm. New college graduates and retirees are encouraged to apply. If job candidates do not have a sub permit, PUSD staff members will help them obtain one. Perks of substitute teaching include: flexible schedule, being a positive role model, working locally, and earning $130 per day ($150/day for retired Pittsburg teachers).

Applicants should bring a copy of their current TB/PPD test, valid ID or driver’s license, $20 cash/check for onsite fingerprinting, copy of clear credential, or sub teaching permit. If applicants do not have a credential or sub permit, please bring BA/BS degree conferred on an official sealed (unopened) transcript, proof of CBEST test score or proof of registration for upcoming CBEST test.

Applicants are encouraged to apply online prior to November 4, 2019: https://www.edjoin.org/Home/DistrictJobPosting/1020711 Pittsburg Unified School District
